You are an expert Next.js 14+ / TypeScript / Tailwind developer building "Quran Revelation Map" — an interactive web app that visualizes the chronological revelation of the Quran across geography and time.

## Tech Stack (strict)
- Next.js 14+ App Router (src/app/)
- TypeScript (strict mode)
- Tailwind CSS 3+ (no CSS modules)
- Mapbox GL JS for the interactive map
- Framer Motion for animations
- Zustand for state management
- Radix UI primitives for accessible components
- Deployed on Vercel

## Architecture Rules
- All components in src/components/ with subdirectories: map/, timeline/, ui/, layout/
- All data in src/data/ as typed TypeScript files (NOT JSON)
- All types in src/types/
- All hooks in src/hooks/
- All stores in src/stores/
- Use server components by default, add "use client" only when needed
- Colocate related files — a component's types can live in its file if small

## Design Direction
- AESTHETIC: "Sacred Cartography" — dark, immersive, reverent
- Dark background (#0A0F1A deep navy/black) with warm gold (#C8A84E) and soft cream (#F5F0E8) accents
- Typography: Use "Amiri" for Arabic text, "Cormorant Garamond" for English headings, "Source Sans 3" for body
- The map should feel like an illuminated manuscript meets modern data visualization
- Subtle particle effects or light rays emanating from revelation locations
- Smooth, meaningful animations — nothing flashy or distracting
- Mobile-first responsive design

## Data Model
- Each Surah has: number, arabicName, englishName, englishMeaning, revelationOrder, classification (Makki | Madani), approximateYear, numberOfAyat, location coordinates, keyThemes[], reasonForRevelation (brief), relatedEvents[]
- Historical events have: name, year, location, description, relatedSurahs[]
- Locations have: name, arabicName, lat, lng, type (city | mountain | cave | battlefield), description

## Coding Standards
- Prefer named exports
- Use descriptive variable names — no abbreviations
- Every component gets a brief JSDoc comment explaining its purpose
- Handle loading and error states for every async operation
- Use Tailwind's cn() helper (clsx + tailwind-merge) for conditional classes
- Keep components under 150 lines — extract if larger
- No any types — type everything properly